<div class="q-panel active" id="qp-0">
  <div class="math-layout">
    <div class="problem-panel">
      <div class="panel-label">Problem</div>
      <div class="problem-text">In a right triangle, cos(x°) = 5/13.</div>
      <div class="hint">Use the complementary angle identity: sin(90° − x°) = cos(x°). The sine of the complementary angle equals the cosine of the original angle — no calculation required.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-panel-inner">
      <div class="q-label">Question 1 · Complementary Angles</div>
      <div class="q-text">What is the value of <strong>sin(90° − x°)</strong>?</div>
      <div class="opts" id="opts-0">
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(0,this,'A')"><span class="opt-l">A</span>12/13</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(0,this,'B')"><span class="opt-l">B</span>5/13</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(0,this,'C')"><span class="opt-l">C</span>5/12</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(0,this,'D')"><span class="opt-l">D</span>13/5</div>
      </div>
      <div class="q-actions">
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-0-ok"><strong>Correct! 5/13</strong><div class="fb-work">Complementary identity: sin(90°−x°) = cos(x°)<br>cos(x°) = 5/13<br>∴ sin(90°−x°) = 5/13 ✓<br><br>No calculation needed — just apply the identity directly.<br>Option A (12/13) would be sin(x°), not sin(90°−x°).</div></div>
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-0-fail"><strong>Not quite.</strong> The complementary identity states: sin(90°−θ) = cos(θ). So sin(90°−x°) equals cos(x°) directly — what is cos(x°)?<div class="fb-work">sin(90°−x°) = cos(x°) = 5/13</div></div>
        <button class="btn-check" id="btn-0" onclick="check(0,'B')" disabled>Check answer</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="q-panel" id="qp-1">
  <div class="math-layout">
    <div class="problem-panel">
      <div class="panel-label">Problem</div>
      <div class="problem-text">A surveyor stands 80 meters from the base of a building and measures the angle of elevation to the top to be 38°.</div>
      <div class="hint">The height is opposite the 38° angle; the horizontal distance (80 m) is adjacent. Use tan(38°) = opposite/adjacent = height/80. Solve: height = 80 × tan(38°).</div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-panel-inner">
      <div class="q-label">Question 2 · Trig Application</div>
      <div class="q-text">What is the approximate height of the building? (tan 38° ≈ 0.781)</div>
      <div class="opts" id="opts-1">
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(1,this,'A')"><span class="opt-l">A</span>approximately 51 meters</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(1,this,'B')"><span class="opt-l">B</span>approximately 62 meters</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(1,this,'C')"><span class="opt-l">C</span>approximately 78 meters</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(1,this,'D')"><span class="opt-l">D</span>approximately 102 meters</div>
      </div>
      <div class="q-actions">
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-1-ok"><strong>Correct! ≈ 62 meters</strong><div class="fb-work">tan(38°) = height / 80<br>height = 80 × tan(38°)<br>= 80 × 0.781<br>= 62.48 ≈ 62 meters ✓</div></div>
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-1-fail"><strong>Not quite.</strong> Height is opposite to 38°; distance 80m is adjacent. Use tangent: height = 80 × tan(38°) = 80 × 0.781.<div class="fb-work">= 62.5 ≈ 62 meters</div></div>
        <button class="btn-check" id="btn-1" onclick="check(1,'B')" disabled>Check answer</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="q-panel" id="qp-2">
  <div class="math-layout">
    <div class="problem-panel">
      <div class="panel-label">Problem</div>
      <div class="problem-text">In a right triangle, sin(θ) = 7/25.</div>
      <div class="hint">Use the Pythagorean identity: sin²θ + cos²θ = 1. Substitute sin θ = 7/25, solve for cos θ. Then use tan θ = sin θ / cos θ.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-panel-inner">
      <div class="q-label">Question 3 · Pythagorean Identity</div>
      <div class="q-text">What is the value of <strong>tan(θ)</strong>?</div>
      <div class="opts" id="opts-2">
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(2,this,'A')"><span class="opt-l">A</span>7/24</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(2,this,'B')"><span class="opt-l">B</span>24/25</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(2,this,'C')"><span class="opt-l">C</span>7/25</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(2,this,'D')"><span class="opt-l">D</span>25/7</div>
      </div>
      <div class="q-actions">
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-2-ok"><strong>Correct! tan θ = 7/24</strong><div class="fb-work">sin²θ + cos²θ = 1<br>(7/25)² + cos²θ = 1<br>49/625 + cos²θ = 1<br>cos²θ = 576/625 → cos θ = 24/25<br><br>tan θ = sin θ/cos θ = (7/25)/(24/25) = 7/24 ✓<br><br>Or: 7-24-25 is a Pythagorean triple!<br>sin=7/25 → opposite=7, hyp=25 → adjacent=24<br>tan = 7/24 ✓</div></div>
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-2-fail"><strong>Not quite.</strong> Use sin²θ + cos²θ = 1 to find cos θ. Then tan θ = sin θ / cos θ. Alternatively, recognize 7-24-25 as a Pythagorean triple.<div class="fb-work">cos θ = 24/25 · tan θ = 7/24</div></div>
        <button class="btn-check" id="btn-2" onclick="check(2,'A')" disabled>Check answer</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

