<div class="q-panel active" id="qp-0">
  <div class="math-layout">
    <div class="problem-panel">
      <div class="panel-label">Problem</div>
      <div class="problem-text">A circle in the xy-plane has the equation:</div>
      <span class="math-eq">(x + 4)² + (y − 7)² = 25</span>
      <div class="hint">Rewrite (x + 4)² as (x − (−4))² to identify h = −4. The center is (h, k) = (−4, 7) and radius² = 25 so r = 5.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-panel-inner">
      <div class="q-label">Question 1 · Circle Equation</div>
      <div class="q-text">What are the <strong>center</strong> and <strong>radius</strong> of this circle?</div>
      <div class="opts" id="opts-0">
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(0,this,'A')"><span class="opt-l">A</span>Center (4, −7), radius 5</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(0,this,'B')"><span class="opt-l">B</span>Center (−4, 7), radius 5</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(0,this,'C')"><span class="opt-l">C</span>Center (−4, 7), radius 25</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(0,this,'D')"><span class="opt-l">D</span>Center (4, −7), radius 25</div>
      </div>
      <div class="q-actions">
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-0-ok"><strong>Correct! Center (−4, 7), radius 5</strong><div class="fb-work">(x + 4)² = (x − (−4))² → h = −4<br>(y − 7)² → k = 7<br>r² = 25 → r = 5<br>Center: (−4, 7) · Radius: 5 ✓</div></div>
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-0-fail"><strong>Not quite.</strong> In (x − h)² + (y − k)² = r², the center is (h, k). Watch signs: (x + 4) = (x − (−4)) → h = −4. And r² = 25 → r = 5, not 25.<div class="fb-work">Center (−4, 7), radius 5</div></div>
        <button class="btn-check" id="btn-0" onclick="check(0,'B')" disabled>Check answer</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="q-panel" id="qp-1">
  <div class="math-layout">
    <div class="problem-panel">
      <div class="panel-label">Problem</div>
      <div class="problem-text">A circle has center O and radius 9. Points A and B are on the circle. The central angle AOB measures 140°.</div>
      <div class="hint">Arc length = (central angle/360) × 2πr = (140/360) × 2π(9). The inscribed angle that subtends the same arc = half the central angle = 70°.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-panel-inner">
      <div class="q-label">Question 2 · Arc Length & Inscribed Angle</div>
      <div class="q-text">What is the arc length of arc AB? (Leave in terms of π.)</div>
      <div class="opts" id="opts-1">
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(1,this,'A')"><span class="opt-l">A</span>7π</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(1,this,'B')"><span class="opt-l">B</span>9π</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(1,this,'C')"><span class="opt-l">C</span>14π</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(1,this,'D')"><span class="opt-l">D</span>63π/5</div>
      </div>
      <div class="q-actions">
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-1-ok"><strong>Correct! 7π</strong><div class="fb-work">Arc length = (140/360) × 2π(9)<br>= (7/18) × 18π<br>= 7π ✓</div></div>
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-1-fail"><strong>Not quite.</strong> Arc = (θ/360) × 2πr = (140/360) × 2π(9). Simplify 140/360 = 7/18, and 2(9) = 18.<div class="fb-work">(7/18) × 18π = 7π</div></div>
        <button class="btn-check" id="btn-1" onclick="check(1,'A')" disabled>Check answer</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="q-panel" id="qp-2">
  <div class="math-layout">
    <div class="problem-panel">
      <div class="panel-label">Problem</div>
      <div class="problem-text">Find the center and radius of the circle:</div>
      <span class="math-eq">x² + y² − 10x + 6y + 18 = 0</span>
      <div class="hint">Group and complete the square: (x²−10x___) + (y²+6y___) = −18. Add (5)²=25 and (3)²=9 to both sides. Then write in standard form.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-panel-inner">
      <div class="q-label">Question 3 · Completing the Square</div>
      <div class="q-text">What is the <strong>radius</strong> of this circle?</div>
      <div class="opts" id="opts-2">
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(2,this,'A')"><span class="opt-l">A</span>4</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(2,this,'B')"><span class="opt-l">B</span>√16</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(2,this,'C')"><span class="opt-l">C</span>√34</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(2,this,'D')"><span class="opt-l">D</span>√18</div>
      </div>
      <div class="q-actions">
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-2-ok"><strong>Correct! radius = 4 (= √16)</strong><div class="fb-work">(x²−10x) + (y²+6y) = −18<br>Add 25 and 9 to both sides:<br>(x−5)² + (y+3)² = −18+25+9 = 16<br>r² = 16 → r = 4 ✓<br>Center: (5, −3)</div></div>
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-2-fail"><strong>Not quite.</strong> Complete the square: add (10/2)²=25 and (6/2)²=9 to both sides. The right side becomes −18+25+9=16. So r²=16, r=4.<div class="fb-work">(x−5)²+(y+3)²=16 → r=4</div></div>
        <button class="btn-check" id="btn-2" onclick="check(2,'A')" disabled>Check answer</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

