<div class="q-tabs">
  <button class="q-tab active" onclick="switchQ(0,this)">Question 1</button>
  <button class="q-tab" onclick="switchQ(1,this)">Question 2</button>
  <button class="q-tab" onclick="switchQ(2,this)">Question 3</button>
</div>

<div class="q-panel active" id="qp-0">
  <div class="math-layout">
    <div class="problem-panel">
      <div class="panel-label">Problem</div>
      <div class="problem-text">Points A = (2, −1) and B = (8, 7) are endpoints of a segment.</div>
      <div class="hint">Distance: √[(8−2)² + (7−(−1))²] = √[36+64] = √100. Midpoint: ((2+8)/2, (−1+7)/2).</div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-panel-inner">
      <div class="q-label">Question 1 · Distance & Midpoint</div>
      <div class="q-text">What is the <strong>midpoint</strong> of segment AB?</div>
      <div class="opts" id="opts-0">
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(0,this,'A')"><span class="opt-l">A</span>(5, 3)</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(0,this,'B')"><span class="opt-l">B</span>(6, 8)</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(0,this,'C')"><span class="opt-l">C</span>(3, 4)</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(0,this,'D')"><span class="opt-l">D</span>(5, 4)</div>
      </div>
      <div class="q-actions">
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-0-ok"><strong>Correct! (5, 3)</strong><div class="fb-work">M_x = (2+8)/2 = 10/2 = 5<br>M_y = (−1+7)/2 = 6/2 = 3<br>Midpoint = (5, 3) ✓<br><br>Bonus: distance AB = √[(6)²+(8)²] = √100 = 10 (6-8-10 triple)</div></div>
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-0-fail"><strong>Not quite.</strong> Midpoint: average the x-coordinates and average the y-coordinates. (2+8)/2 = 5 and (−1+7)/2 = 3.<div class="fb-work">Midpoint = (5, 3)</div></div>
        <button class="btn-check" id="btn-0" onclick="check(0,'A')" disabled>Check answer</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="q-panel" id="qp-1">
  <div class="math-layout">
    <div class="problem-panel">
      <div class="panel-label">Problem</div>
      <div class="problem-text">Point P divides segment from C = (0, 0) to D = (10, 15) in the ratio 2:3 (measured from C).</div>
      <div class="hint">Use partition formula: P_x = 0 + 2/(2+3) × (10−0) = 2/5 × 10 = 4. P_y = 0 + 2/5 × 15 = 6.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-panel-inner">
      <div class="q-label">Question 2 · Partition Point</div>
      <div class="q-text">What are the coordinates of point <strong>P</strong>?</div>
      <div class="opts" id="opts-1">
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(1,this,'A')"><span class="opt-l">A</span>(4, 6)</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(1,this,'B')"><span class="opt-l">B</span>(6, 9)</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(1,this,'C')"><span class="opt-l">C</span>(5, 7.5)</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(1,this,'D')"><span class="opt-l">D</span>(2, 3)</div>
      </div>
      <div class="q-actions">
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-1-ok"><strong>Correct! (4, 6)</strong><div class="fb-work">Fraction from C: 2/(2+3) = 2/5<br>P_x = 0 + (2/5)(10−0) = 4<br>P_y = 0 + (2/5)(15−0) = 6<br>P = (4, 6) ✓<br><br>Check: C to P distance = √(16+36)=√52, P to D = √(36+81)=√117. Ratio: √52:√117 ≈ 2:3 ✓</div></div>
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-1-fail"><strong>Not quite.</strong> Move 2/(2+3) = 2/5 of the way from C to D. x: 0 + (2/5)(10) = 4. y: 0 + (2/5)(15) = 6.<div class="fb-work">P = (4, 6)</div></div>
        <button class="btn-check" id="btn-1" onclick="check(1,'A')" disabled>Check answer</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="q-panel" id="qp-2">
  <div class="math-layout">
    <div class="problem-panel">
      <div class="panel-label">Problem</div>
      <div class="problem-text">Triangle ABC has vertices at A = (0, 0), B = (6, 0), and C = (4, 5).</div>
      <div class="hint">Area of triangle with one side on x-axis: base AB = 6 (horizontal distance). Height = y-coordinate of C = 5. Area = ½ × base × height.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-panel-inner">
      <div class="q-label">Question 3 · Area in Coordinate Plane</div>
      <div class="q-text">What is the <strong>area</strong> of triangle ABC?</div>
      <div class="opts" id="opts-2">
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(2,this,'A')"><span class="opt-l">A</span>12</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(2,this,'B')"><span class="opt-l">B</span>15</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(2,this,'C')"><span class="opt-l">C</span>20</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(2,this,'D')"><span class="opt-l">D</span>30</div>
      </div>
      <div class="q-actions">
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-2-ok"><strong>Correct! 15</strong><div class="fb-work">Base AB lies on x-axis: length = 6−0 = 6<br>Height = perpendicular distance from C to x-axis = y-coordinate of C = 5<br>Area = ½ × 6 × 5 = 15 ✓</div></div>
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-2-fail"><strong>Not quite.</strong> Since A and B both have y = 0, AB is the base along the x-axis. Its length is 6. The height is C's y-coordinate (5). Area = ½bh.<div class="fb-work">½ × 6 × 5 = 15</div></div>
        <button class="btn-check" id="btn-2" onclick="check(2,'B')" disabled>Check answer</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

