<div class="calc-badge">🖩 Calculator allowed</div>
<div class="tag">SAT Math · Module 4 · Lesson 4.12</div>
<div class="lesson-title">Probability & Expected Value</div>
<div class="lesson-sub">Go deeper on probability — multi-event problems, independent vs. dependent events, geometric probability, and expected value in complex real-world contexts.</div>
<div class="dur-row"><span><b>13 min</b> read</span><span><b>3</b> practice questions</span><span><b>+20 pts</b> on completion</span></div>

<div class="card">
  <div class="sec-title">Advanced probability concepts</div>
  <div class="formula-box">
    <div class="formula">
      P(A and B) = P(A) × P(B|A) &nbsp;[general]<br>
      P(A and B) = P(A) × P(B) &nbsp;[if independent]<br>
      P(A or B) = P(A) + P(B) − P(A and B)<br>
      E(X) = Σ xᵢ · P(xᵢ) &nbsp;[expected value]
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="concept-grid">
    <div class="c-card">
      <div class="c-title">Independent events</div>
      <div class="c-body">Events A and B are independent if P(A|B) = P(A) — knowing B doesn't change A's probability. Multiply probabilities directly.</div>
      <div class="c-ex">Two coin flips: P(HH) = ½ × ½ = ¼<br>Drawing with replacement = independent</div>
    </div>
    <div class="c-card">
      <div class="c-title">Dependent events</div>
      <div class="c-body">Without replacement, the second event depends on the first. Use conditional probability: adjust the denominator after the first draw.</div>
      <div class="c-ex">Draw 2 reds from 4R, 3B without replacement:<br>P = 4/7 × 3/6 = 12/42 = 2/7</div>
    </div>
    <div class="c-card">
      <div class="c-title">Geometric probability</div>
      <div class="c-body">P(landing in region) = area of region / total area. Used when a random point is selected in a geometric figure.</div>
      <div class="c-ex">Dart hits 8×8 board randomly. Circle of r=2 inside.<br>P(circle) = π(4)/64 = π/16 ≈ 0.196</div>
    </div>
    <div class="c-card">
      <div class="c-title">Expected value</div>
      <div class="c-body">The long-run average outcome. Multiply each outcome by its probability and sum. A fair game has expected value = 0.</div>
      <div class="c-ex">Win $5 (P=0.3), lose $2 (P=0.7):<br>E = 5(0.3) + (−2)(0.7) = 1.5−1.4 = $0.10</div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="example-box">
    <div class="example-label">Worked example — dependent events without replacement</div>
    <div class="example-text">
      A bag has 5 red and 3 blue chips. Two are drawn without replacement. What is P(both red)?<br><br>
      <span class="fb-work">P(first red) = 5/8</span><br>
      <span class="fb-work">P(second red | first was red) = 4/7 &nbsp;(4 reds remain out of 7)</span><br>
      <span class="fb-work">P(both red) = 5/8 × 4/7 = 20/56 = 5/14</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="card">
  <div class="sec-title">SAT strategy tips</div>
  <div class="tips-grid">
    <div class="tip"><div class="tip-title">With replacement = independent; without = dependent</div><div class="tip-body">The phrase "without replacement" always means dependent events — adjust the denominator after each draw. "With replacement" means independent — the denominator stays the same every time.</div></div>
    <div class="tip"><div class="tip-title">Geometric probability: set up area ratio</div><div class="tip-body">For geometric probability problems, find the ratio of the favorable area to the total area. Express areas in terms of the given dimensions before simplifying.</div></div>
    <div class="tip"><div class="tip-title">Expected value can be negative</div><div class="tip-body">If expected value is negative, the game is unfavorable on average. The SAT may ask "how much should the ticket cost to make this a fair game?" — set E = 0 and solve for the cost.</div></div>
    <div class="tip"><div class="tip-title">"At least one" — use complementary probability</div><div class="tip-body">P(at least one event) = 1 − P(none at all). For "at least one success in n trials": 1 − P(all failures) = 1 − (1−p)ⁿ. This is always faster than summing individual cases.</div></div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="sec-title" style="margin-bottom:.75rem">Practice questions</div>
<div class="q-tabs">
  <button class="q-tab active" onclick="switchQ(0,this)">Question 1</button>
  <button class="q-tab" onclick="switchQ(1,this)">Question 2</button>
  <button class="q-tab" onclick="switchQ(2,this)">Question 3</button>
</div>

<div class="q-panel active" id="qp-0">
  <div class="math-layout">
    <div class="problem-panel">
      <div class="panel-label">Problem</div>
      <div class="problem-text">A box contains 4 green, 3 yellow, and 2 purple balls. Two balls are drawn without replacement.</div>
      <div class="hint">Without replacement = dependent events. P(first green) = 4/9. After drawing one green, 3 green balls remain out of 8 total. P(second green | first green) = 3/8.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-panel-inner">
      <div class="q-label">Question 1 · Dependent Events</div>
      <div class="q-text">What is the probability that <strong>both balls drawn are green</strong>?</div>
      <div class="opts" id="opts-0">
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(0,this,'A')"><span class="opt-l">A</span>16/81</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(0,this,'B')"><span class="opt-l">B</span>1/6</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(0,this,'C')"><span class="opt-l">C</span>4/9</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(0,this,'D')"><span class="opt-l">D</span>2/9</div>
      </div>
      <div class="q-actions">
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-0-ok"><strong>Correct! 1/6</strong><div class="fb-work">P(1st green) = 4/9<br>P(2nd green | 1st green) = 3/8<br>P(both green) = 4/9 × 3/8 = 12/72 = 1/6 ✓<br><br>Option A (16/81) is for WITH replacement: (4/9)² = 16/81.</div></div>
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-0-fail"><strong>Not quite.</strong> Without replacement: first draw has 9 balls, second draw has 8. If first is green (4 out of 9), then 3 greens remain out of 8.<div class="fb-work">4/9 × 3/8 = 12/72 = 1/6</div></div>
        <button class="btn-check" id="btn-0" onclick="check(0,'B')" disabled>Check answer</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
