</div>

<div class="q-panel" id="qp-1">
  <div class="math-layout">
    <div class="problem-panel">
      <div class="panel-label">Problem</div>
      <div class="problem-text">Multiply:</div>
      <span class="math-eq">(3 + 2i)(4 − 5i)</span>
      <div class="hint">Use FOIL: First=3×4=12, Outer=3×(−5i)=−15i, Inner=2i×4=8i, Last=2i×(−5i)=−10i². Replace i²=−1: −10i²=+10.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-panel-inner">
      <div class="q-label">Question 2 · Multiplying Complex Numbers</div>
      <div class="q-text">Which expression equals <strong>(3 + 2i)(4 − 5i)</strong>?</div>
      <div class="opts" id="opts-1">
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(1,this,'A')"><span class="opt-l">A</span>2 − 7i</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(1,this,'B')"><span class="opt-l">B</span>22 − 7i</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(1,this,'C')"><span class="opt-l">C</span>12 − 7i</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(1,this,'D')"><span class="opt-l">D</span>22 + 7i</div>
      </div>
      <div class="q-actions">
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-1-ok"><strong>Correct! 22 − 7i</strong><div class="fb-work">FOIL: 12 − 15i + 8i − 10i²<br>= 12 − 7i − 10(−1)<br>= 12 − 7i + 10<br>= 22 − 7i ✓</div></div>
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-1-fail"><strong>Not quite.</strong> FOIL then replace i²=−1: (3)(4)+(3)(−5i)+(2i)(4)+(2i)(−5i) = 12−15i+8i−10i². Now −10i² = +10. Combine.<div class="fb-work">12 + 10 = 22 (real) · −15i+8i = −7i → 22−7i</div></div>
        <button class="btn-check" id="btn-1" onclick="check(1,'B')" disabled>Check answer</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="q-panel" id="qp-2">
  <div class="math-layout">
    <div class="problem-panel">
      <div class="panel-label">Problem</div>
      <div class="problem-text">The expression (a + bi)² = 21 + 20i, where a and b are real numbers. Find a and b.</div>
      <div class="hint">Expand: (a+bi)² = a² + 2abi + b²i² = (a²−b²) + 2abi. Match real parts: a²−b²=21. Match imaginary parts: 2ab=20 → ab=10. Solve the system.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-panel-inner">
      <div class="q-label">Question 3 · Complex Equations</div>
      <div class="q-text">What are the values of <strong>a</strong> and <strong>b</strong>?</div>
      <div class="opts" id="opts-2">
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(2,this,'A')"><span class="opt-l">A</span>a = 5, b = 2</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(2,this,'B')"><span class="opt-l">B</span>a = 4, b = 3</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(2,this,'C')"><span class="opt-l">C</span>a = 5, b = 3</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(2,this,'D')"><span class="opt-l">D</span>a = 3, b = 4</div>
      </div>
      <div class="q-actions">
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-2-ok"><strong>Correct! a = 5, b = 2</strong><div class="fb-work">(a+bi)² = (a²−b²) + 2abi<br>Real: a²−b² = 21<br>Imaginary: 2ab = 20 → ab = 10 → b = 10/a<br><br>Substitute: a² − (10/a)² = 21<br>a⁴ − 21a² − 100 = 0<br>(a²−25)(a²+4) = 0<br>a² = 25 → a = 5, b = 10/5 = 2 ✓<br>Check: (5+2i)² = 25+20i+4i² = 25+20i−4 = 21+20i ✓</div></div>
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-2-fail"><strong>Not quite.</strong> Expand (a+bi)² and match real and imaginary parts: a²−b²=21 and 2ab=20. From the second equation b=10/a. Substitute into the first.<div class="fb-work">a=5, b=2 → (5+2i)²=21+20i ✓</div></div>
        <button class="btn-check" id="btn-2" onclick="check(2,'A')" disabled>Check answer</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

