<div class="q-panel active" id="qp-0">
  <div class="math-layout">
    <div class="problem-panel">
      <div class="panel-label">Problem</div>
      <div class="problem-text">The table shows a relationship between x and y:</div>
      <table style="width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;margin:.75rem 0;font-size:13px;">
        <tr style="background:#FEF3C7;"><th style="padding:7px 14px;border:1px solid #FDE68A;color:#92400E;font-weight:500;">x</th><th style="padding:7px 14px;border:1px solid #FDE68A;color:#92400E;font-weight:500;">y</th></tr>
        <tr><td style="padding:7px 14px;text-align:center;border:1px solid #e5e7eb;font-family:Georgia,serif;">0</td><td style="padding:7px 14px;text-align:center;border:1px solid #e5e7eb;font-family:Georgia,serif;">3</td></tr>
        <tr><td style="padding:7px 14px;text-align:center;border:1px solid #e5e7eb;font-family:Georgia,serif;">1</td><td style="padding:7px 14px;text-align:center;border:1px solid #e5e7eb;font-family:Georgia,serif;">6</td></tr>
        <tr><td style="padding:7px 14px;text-align:center;border:1px solid #e5e7eb;font-family:Georgia,serif;">2</td><td style="padding:7px 14px;text-align:center;border:1px solid #e5e7eb;font-family:Georgia,serif;">12</td></tr>
        <tr><td style="padding:7px 14px;text-align:center;border:1px solid #e5e7eb;font-family:Georgia,serif;">3</td><td style="padding:7px 14px;text-align:center;border:1px solid #e5e7eb;font-family:Georgia,serif;">24</td></tr>
      </table>
      <div class="hint">Check differences: 3, 6, 12 — not constant. Check ratios: 6/3=2, 12/6=2, 24/12=2 — constant ratio of 2 → exponential. Initial value a=3, base b=2.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-panel-inner">
      <div class="q-label">Question 1 · Identifying the Model</div>
      <div class="q-text">Which equation best models the data?</div>
      <div class="opts" id="opts-0">
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(0,this,'A')"><span class="opt-l">A</span>y = 3x + 3</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(0,this,'B')"><span class="opt-l">B</span>y = 3 · 2ˣ</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(0,this,'C')"><span class="opt-l">C</span>y = 2 · 3ˣ</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(0,this,'D')"><span class="opt-l">D</span>y = 6x − 3</div>
      </div>
      <div class="q-actions">
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-0-ok"><strong>Correct! y = 3 · 2ˣ</strong><div class="fb-work">Ratios: 6/3=2, 12/6=2, 24/12=2 → constant ratio → exponential<br>At x=0: y=3 → a=3<br>Ratio = base = 2<br>f(x) = 3·2ˣ ✓<br>Check: f(1)=6✓, f(2)=12✓, f(3)=24✓</div></div>
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-0-fail"><strong>Not quite.</strong> Check if differences or ratios are constant. Differences: 3,6,12 — not constant. Ratios: 6/3=2, 12/6=2 — constant! So it's exponential with initial value 3 and base 2.<div class="fb-work">f(x) = 3·2ˣ</div></div>
        <button class="btn-check" id="btn-0" onclick="check(0,'B')" disabled>Check answer</button>
      </div>
    </div>
