    <div class="tip"><div class="tip-title">Work rates: add rates, not times</div><div class="tip-body">If two workers work simultaneously, add their rates (jobs/hour), not their times. Rate A + Rate B = Combined rate. Then time = 1/combined rate. Adding times together is a classic error.</div></div>
    <div class="tip"><div class="tip-title">Average speed ≠ average of two speeds</div><div class="tip-body">For a round trip or two-segment journey at different speeds, average speed = total distance / total time. Calculate each segment's time using d=rt, sum the times, then divide total distance by total time.</div></div>
