</div>

<div class="q-panel active" id="qp-0">
  <div class="math-layout">
    <div class="problem-panel">
      <div class="panel-label">System</div>
      <span class="math-eq">y ≤ 2x + 4</span>
      <span class="math-eq">y > −x + 1</span>
      <div class="hint">To check if a point is in the solution region, substitute it into BOTH inequalities. The point must satisfy both. Try each answer choice.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-panel-inner">
      <div class="q-label">Question 1 · Solution Region</div>
      <div class="q-text">Which point <strong>(x, y)</strong> lies in the solution region of the system?</div>
      <div class="opts" id="opts-0">
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(0,this,'A')"><span class="opt-l">A</span>(0, 5)</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(0,this,'B')"><span class="opt-l">B</span>(3, 2)</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(0,this,'C')"><span class="opt-l">C</span>(−2, 0)</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(0,this,'D')"><span class="opt-l">D</span>(1, −1)</div>
      </div>
      <div class="q-actions">
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-0-ok"><strong>Correct! (3, 2)</strong><div class="fb-work">Check (3, 2):<br>y ≤ 2x+4: 2 ≤ 2(3)+4 = 10 ✓<br>y > −x+1: 2 > −3+1 = −2 ✓ Both satisfied!<br><br>Check (0,5): 5 ≤ 4? No ✗<br>Check (−2,0): 0 > 2+1=3? No ✗<br>Check (1,−1): −1 ≤ 6 ✓ but −1 > 0? No ✗</div></div>
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-0-fail"><strong>Not quite.</strong> Substitute each option into both inequalities. The solution must satisfy y ≤ 2x+4 AND y > −x+1. Try (3, 2): does it satisfy both?<div class="fb-work">(3,2): 2≤10 ✓ and 2>−2 ✓ → in the region</div></div>
        <button class="btn-check" id="btn-0" onclick="check(0,'B')" disabled>Check answer</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="q-panel" id="qp-1">
  <div class="math-layout">
    <div class="problem-panel">
      <div class="panel-label">Problem</div>
      <div class="problem-text">A store sells T-shirts (t) for $15 each and hats (h) for $25 each. A customer wants to spend at most $150 total and buy at least 4 items altogether.</div>
      <div class="hint">Write two inequalities: spending → 15t + 25h ≤ 150. Items → t + h ≥ 4. Non-negative: t ≥ 0, h ≥ 0. Then check which combination satisfies all constraints.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-panel-inner">
      <div class="q-label">Question 2 · Real-World Inequality System</div>
      <div class="q-text">Which combination satisfies <strong>all</strong> constraints?</div>
      <div class="opts" id="opts-1">
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(1,this,'A')"><span class="opt-l">A</span>t = 2, h = 5 (2 T-shirts, 5 hats)</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(1,this,'B')"><span class="opt-l">B</span>t = 6, h = 2 (6 T-shirts, 2 hats)</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(1,this,'C')"><span class="opt-l">C</span>t = 4, h = 4 (4 T-shirts, 4 hats)</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(1,this,'D')"><span class="opt-l">D</span>t = 8, h = 0 (8 T-shirts, 0 hats)</div>
      </div>
      <div class="q-actions">
