      <div class="problem-text">Find the value(s) of b for which the equation has exactly one real solution.</div>
      <div class="hint">Exactly one solution means the discriminant = 0: b²−4(3)(12) = 0. Solve: b²−144=0 → b=±12.</div>
    </div>
