      <div class="problem-text">A point P is located at (3, 7) in the xy-plane. A circle has center (−1, 4) and radius 6.</div>
      <div class="hint">Find the distance from P to the center using the distance formula. Then compare to the radius: if distance &lt; r, P is inside; if distance = r, P is on; if distance &gt; r, P is outside.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-panel-inner">
      <div class="q-label">Question 2 · Point and Circle</div>
      <div class="q-text">Is point P inside, on, or outside the circle?</div>
      <div class="opts" id="opts-1">
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(1,this,'A')"><span class="opt-l">A</span>Inside the circle (distance &lt; 6)</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(1,this,'B')"><span class="opt-l">B</span>On the circle (distance = 6)</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(1,this,'C')"><span class="opt-l">C</span>Outside the circle (distance &gt; 6)</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(1,this,'D')"><span class="opt-l">D</span>Cannot be determined without the equation</div>
