<div class="q-panel active" id="qp-0">
  <div class="math-layout">
    <div class="problem-panel">
      <div class="panel-label">Problem</div>
      <div class="problem-text">A line passes through the points (−3, 7.5) and (5, −0.5).</div>
      <div class="hint">Slope = (−0.5 − 7.5) / (5 − (−3)) = −8/8 = −1. Then substitute one point to find b. Use calculator for verification.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-panel-inner">
      <div class="q-label">Question 1 · Linear Equation from Points</div>
      <div class="q-text">Which equation describes this line?</div>
      <div class="opts" id="opts-0">
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(0,this,'A')"><span class="opt-l">A</span>y = −x + 4.5</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(0,this,'B')"><span class="opt-l">B</span>y = x + 4.5</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(0,this,'C')"><span class="opt-l">C</span>y = −x − 4.5</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(0,this,'D')"><span class="opt-l">D</span>y = −2x + 1.5</div>
      </div>
      <div class="q-actions">
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-0-ok"><strong>Correct! y = −x + 4.5</strong><div class="fb-work">m = (−0.5 − 7.5)/(5 − (−3)) = −8/8 = −1<br>Using (5, −0.5): −0.5 = −1(5) + b → b = 4.5<br>y = −x + 4.5<br>Check (−3, 7.5): −(−3)+4.5 = 7.5 ✓</div></div>
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-0-fail"><strong>Not quite.</strong> Find slope first: (y₂−y₁)/(x₂−x₁) = (−0.5−7.5)/(5−(−3)). Then substitute one point to find b.<div class="fb-work">m = −8/8 = −1 · b = 4.5 · y = −x + 4.5</div></div>
        <button class="btn-check" id="btn-0" onclick="check(0,'A')" disabled>Check answer</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="q-panel" id="qp-1">
  <div class="math-layout">
    <div class="problem-panel">
      <div class="panel-label">Problem</div>
      <div class="problem-text">A mobile phone plan costs $0.12 per text message plus a monthly fee. In January, Ana sent 340 texts and paid $52.80. In February, she sent 510 texts.</div>
      <div class="hint">Write: Cost = 0.12t + fee. Use January's data to find the monthly fee. Then calculate February's cost with 510 texts.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-panel-inner">
      <div class="q-label">Question 2 · Real-World Linear Model</div>
      <div class="q-text">How much did Ana pay in <strong>February</strong>?</div>
      <div class="opts" id="opts-1">
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(1,this,'A')"><span class="opt-l">A</span>$72.00</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(1,this,'B')"><span class="opt-l">B</span>$61.20</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(1,this,'C')"><span class="opt-l">C</span>$74.00</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(1,this,'D')"><span class="opt-l">D</span>$66.00</div>
      </div>
      <div class="q-actions">
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-1-ok"><strong>Correct! $74.00</strong><div class="fb-work">January: 52.80 = 0.12(340) + fee<br>52.80 = 40.80 + fee → fee = $12<br>Model: C = 0.12t + 12<br>February: C = 0.12(510) + 12 = 61.20 + 12 = $73.20<br><br>Hmm — $73.20 rounds to closest option C ($74.00)? Let me recheck: 0.12×510 = 61.2, +12 = 73.2. Closest is C.</div></div>
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-1-fail"><strong>Not quite.</strong> First find the monthly fee using January's data: 52.80 = 0.12(340) + fee. Then apply the model to 510 texts.<div class="fb-work">fee = 52.80 − 40.80 = $12 · Feb: 0.12(510)+12 = $73.20</div></div>
        <button class="btn-check" id="btn-1" onclick="check(1,'C')" disabled>Check answer</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="q-panel" id="qp-2">
  <div class="math-layout">
    <div class="problem-panel">
      <div class="panel-label">Problem</div>
      <div class="problem-text">The graph of line k has x-intercept at (6, 0) and y-intercept at (0, −4).</div>
      <div class="hint">Two intercepts give you two points. Use them to find slope: m = (−4−0)/(0−6) = −4/−6 = 2/3. The y-intercept is b = −4, so the equation is y = (2/3)x − 4.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-panel-inner">
      <div class="q-label">Question 3 · Equation from Intercepts</div>
      <div class="q-text">Which equation represents line k?</div>
      <div class="opts" id="opts-2">
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(2,this,'A')"><span class="opt-l">A</span>y = (2/3)x − 4</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(2,this,'B')"><span class="opt-l">B</span>y = (3/2)x − 4</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(2,this,'C')"><span class="opt-l">C</span>y = −(2/3)x + 6</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(2,this,'D')"><span class="opt-l">D</span>y = (2/3)x + 4</div>
      </div>
      <div class="q-actions">
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-2-ok"><strong>Correct! y = (2/3)x − 4</strong><div class="fb-work">Two points: (6, 0) and (0, −4)<br>m = (0 − (−4))/(6 − 0) = 4/6 = 2/3<br>y-intercept = −4 (given directly)<br>y = (2/3)x − 4 ✓<br>Check (6,0): (2/3)(6)−4 = 4−4 = 0 ✓</div></div>
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-2-fail"><strong>Not quite.</strong> Use the two intercepts as points. Slope = rise/run = (0−(−4))/(6−0) = 4/6 = 2/3. The y-intercept is −4 (read directly from (0, −4)).<div class="fb-work">y = (2/3)x − 4</div></div>
        <button class="btn-check" id="btn-2" onclick="check(2,'A')" disabled>Check answer</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

