<div class="lesson-title">Quadratic Functions</div>
<div class="lesson-sub">Apply quadratic skills from Module 3 to complex real-world contexts — projectile motion, revenue models, and area problems — where the calculator handles messy arithmetic so you can focus on setup and interpretation.</div>
<div class="dur-row"><span><b>13 min</b> read</span><span><b>3</b> practice questions</span><span><b>+20 pts</b> on completion</span></div>

<div class="card">
  <div class="sec-title">Three forms — quick reference</div>
  <div class="forms-grid">
    <div class="form-card" style="background:#FEF3C7;">
      <div class="form-title" style="color:#92400E;">Standard form</div>
      <div class="form-eq">ax² + bx + c</div>
      <div class="form-body">y-intercept = c directly. Use quadratic formula to find roots. Axis of symmetry: x = −b/(2a).</div>
    </div>
    <div class="form-card" style="background:#f9fafb;">
      <div class="form-title">Vertex form</div>
      <div class="form-eq">a(x − h)² + k</div>
      <div class="form-body">Vertex = (h, k) directly. Min/max value = k. Axis = x = h. Best for max/min questions.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="form-card" style="background:#EAF3DE;">
      <div class="form-title" style="color:#27500A;">Factored form</div>
      <div class="form-eq">a(x − r₁)(x − r₂)</div>
      <div class="form-body">Roots = r₁ and r₂ directly. Best for x-intercept questions. Axis of symmetry: x = (r₁ + r₂)/2.</div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="example-box">
    <div class="example-label">Worked example — projectile motion</div>
    <div class="example-text">
      A ball is launched from a platform. Its height (feet) after t seconds is h(t) = −16t² + 48t + 64.<br><br>
      <strong>Maximum height:</strong><br>
      <span class="fb-work">t at vertex = −48/(2×−16) = −48/−32 = 1.5 seconds</span><br>
      <span class="fb-work">h(1.5) = −16(2.25) + 48(1.5) + 64 = −36 + 72 + 64 = 100 feet</span><br><br>
      <strong>When does it hit the ground?</strong> Set h = 0:<br>
      <span class="fb-work">−16t² + 48t + 64 = 0 → t² − 3t − 4 = 0 → (t−4)(t+1) = 0</span><br>
      <span class="fb-work">t = 4 seconds (reject t = −1)</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="card">
