      <div class="problem-text">A circular pizza has a diameter of 16 inches. It is cut into 8 equal slices.</div>
      <div class="hint">Each slice is a sector with central angle 360°/8 = 45°. Radius = 8 inches. Use sector area formula: A = (45/360)πr².</div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-panel-inner">
      <div class="q-label">Question 1 · Sector Area</div>
      <div class="q-text">What is the area of <strong>one slice</strong>? (Leave in terms of π.)</div>
