        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(0,this,'A')"><span class="opt-l">A</span>4π square inches</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(0,this,'B')"><span class="opt-l">B</span>8π square inches</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(0,this,'C')"><span class="opt-l">C</span>2π square inches</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(0,this,'D')"><span class="opt-l">D</span>16π square inches</div>
      </div>
      <div class="q-actions">
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-0-ok"><strong>Correct! 8π square inches</strong><div class="fb-work">Radius = 16/2 = 8 inches<br>Each slice: 360°/8 = 45°<br>Sector area = (45/360) × π × 8²<br>= (1/8) × 64π<br>= 8π square inches ✓</div></div>
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-0-fail"><strong>Not quite.</strong> Each of 8 equal slices has angle 45°. Sector area = (45/360) × π × r². With r = 8: (1/8) × 64π.<div class="fb-work">(1/8) × 64π = 8π sq in</div></div>
        <button class="btn-check" id="btn-0" onclick="check(0,'B')" disabled>Check answer</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="q-panel" id="qp-1">
  <div class="math-layout">
    <div class="problem-panel">
      <div class="panel-label">Problem</div>
      <div class="problem-text">In the figure, two parallel lines are cut by a transversal. One angle measures (3x + 15)° and the co-interior angle (same-side interior) measures (2x + 25)°.</div>
      <div class="hint">Co-interior (same-side interior) angles between parallel lines are supplementary — they add up to 180°. Set up: (3x+15) + (2x+25) = 180.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-panel-inner">
      <div class="q-label">Question 2 · Parallel Lines & Angles</div>
      <div class="q-text">What is the value of <strong>x</strong>?</div>
      <div class="opts" id="opts-1">
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(1,this,'A')"><span class="opt-l">A</span>x = 24</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(1,this,'B')"><span class="opt-l">B</span>x = 28</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(1,this,'C')"><span class="opt-l">C</span>x = 32</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(1,this,'D')"><span class="opt-l">D</span>x = 36</div>
      </div>
      <div class="q-actions">
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-1-ok"><strong>Correct! x = 28</strong><div class="fb-work">Co-interior angles sum to 180°:<br>(3x+15) + (2x+25) = 180<br>5x + 40 = 180<br>5x = 140<br>x = 28 ✓<br>Check: 3(28)+15=99° and 2(28)+25=81° · 99+81=180 ✓</div></div>
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-1-fail"><strong>Not quite.</strong> Co-interior (same-side interior) angles between parallel lines sum to 180°. Set up: (3x+15)+(2x+25)=180.<div class="fb-work">5x+40=180 → 5x=140 → x=28</div></div>
        <button class="btn-check" id="btn-1" onclick="check(1,'B')" disabled>Check answer</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="q-panel" id="qp-2">
  <div class="math-layout">
    <div class="problem-panel">
      <div class="panel-label">Problem</div>
      <div class="problem-text">A garden is shaped like a trapezoid with parallel sides of 12 m and 20 m, and a height of 8 m. A circular fountain with radius 2 m is placed in the center of the garden.</div>
      <div class="hint">Find the trapezoid area using A = ½(b₁+b₂)h, then subtract the circular fountain area A = πr². The planted area is the difference.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-panel-inner">
      <div class="q-label">Question 3 · Composite Area</div>
      <div class="q-text">What is the area of the garden <strong>excluding</strong> the fountain? (Use π ≈ 3.14)</div>
      <div class="opts" id="opts-2">
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(2,this,'A')"><span class="opt-l">A</span>approximately 115.4 m²</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(2,this,'B')"><span class="opt-l">B</span>approximately 128 m²</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(2,this,'C')"><span class="opt-l">C</span>approximately 132 m²</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(2,this,'D')"><span class="opt-l">D</span>approximately 143.4 m²</div>
      </div>
      <div class="q-actions">
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-2-ok"><strong>Correct! ≈ 115.4 m²</strong><div class="fb-work">Trapezoid: A = ½(12+20)×8 = ½(32)(8) = 128 m²<br>Fountain: A = π(2)² = 4π ≈ 12.57 m²<br>Garden area = 128 − 12.57 ≈ 115.4 m² ✓</div></div>
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-2-fail"><strong>Not quite.</strong> Trapezoid area = ½(b₁+b₂)h = ½(12+20)(8) = 128 m². Fountain area = π(2)² ≈ 12.57 m². Subtract.<div class="fb-work">128 − 12.57 ≈ 115.4 m²</div></div>
        <button class="btn-check" id="btn-2" onclick="check(2,'A')" disabled>Check answer</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

